properties.Name: PickListV2
properties.Description:
A document that tells the picker what to pick for an order or customer.

The Pick List usually shows the picking locations, the item (Product) to be picked and the quantity to be picked.

Some Pick Lists are arranged to minimize the time the picker spends moving from location to location.

Pick Lists, depending upon use, may also show the customer's name, address, method of shipment and other information.

Picking is the process of selecting inventory to fill an order and physically removing it from its storage location.    Picking reduces the on-hand balance and the allocation amount for the picking location but does not usually result in the reduction of the inventory facilities total on-hand balance.
